[[File:Musée du Transport Urbain Bruxellois 2.jpg|thumb|250px|Inside the tram museum]]
The '''Brussels Tram Museum''' (officially ''Musée du Transport Urbain Bruxellois'' (French) or ''Museum voor het Stedelijk Vervoer te Brussel'' (Dutch)) is a [[transport museum]] located in an old tram depot in the municipality of [[Woluwe-Saint-Pierre]], [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://visitbrussels.be/bitc/BE_en/museum/2096/tram-museum.do |title=Tram Museum |publisher=visitbrussels.be |accessdate=2015-08-10}}</ref> It displays a collection of trams and buses from different eras in the history of public transport in Brussels.

The museum is situated on the [[Avenue de Tervueren]] 364b opposite [[Woluwe Park]].

