The '''Dovlat Film Fond''' (The State Film Fund of Azerbaijan) is a [[film archive]] funded by the Ministry of Culture and Tourism of [[Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.az/articles/economy/105535|title=Azerbaijan increases salaries in several budget-funded organizations|publisher=News.az|date=1 March 2016|access-date=23 November 2016}}</ref>  It has made formal agreements for co-operation with both the Bulgarian and Lithuanian Film Archives.<ref name="coop" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://azertag.az/en/xeber/AZERBAIJAN_STATE_FILM_FUND_LITHUANIAN_STATE_CENTRAL_ARCHIVE_TO_COOPERATE-593211|title=Azerbaijan State Film Fund, Lithuanian Central Archive to Cooperate|publisher=Azerbaijan State News Agency|date=8 July 2010|access-date=23 November 2016}}</ref> Its president in 2007 was Jamil Gouliyev.<ref name="coop">{{cite web|url=http://azertag.az/en/xeber/AZERBAIJAN_FILM_FUND_TO_COOPERATE_WITH_BULGARIAN_FILM_ARCHIVE_FUNDS_PRESIDENT_GOULIYEV-568454|title=Azerbaijan Film Fund to Cooperate with Bulgarian Film Archive, Fund's President Gouliyev|publisher=Azerbaijan State News Agency|date=19 August 2007|access-date=23 November 2016}}</ref>

