A '''plaint note''' is a legal document, chiefly referred to as such under [[English law]] and that of other [[Commonwealth of Nations|Commonwealth]] nations. It is sent by a court to a defendant to confirm legal action taken against them, and to inform them of their case number. In this way, it is comparable to a [[summons]] in [[American law]].

